[![](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/08/Life_from_behind-800x533.jpg)](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%D0%96%D0%B8%D0%B2%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%B0_%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%B3%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%82_%D0%BE%D1%82%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%B4.jpg)

European bee-eater (Merops apiaster) in [Persina Nature
Park](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persina_Nature_Park), Bulgaria. Photo by
Borilei via Wikimedia Commons, CC BY-SA 4.0.

Bulgarian Wikipedia announced the top 10 photos that will represent the
country in the international photo contest of nature protected areas, “Wiki
Loves Earth.”

The photos were presented August 2, 2017 via a widely shared [special Facebook
post](https://www.facebook.com/WikipediaBG/posts/1552965591421361) which
featured the top 10 photos and links to the original versions. The post also
included special thanks to the [members of the
jury](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Wiki_Loves_Earth_2017_in_Bulgaria),
which include prominent academics from the areas of botany, zoology,
geography, ecology and astrophysics, as well as members with experience in
natural photography.

[![](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/08/Chinari_Strumeshnica-800x534.jpg)](https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%D0%A0%D0%B5%D0%BA%D0%B0_%D0%A1%D1%82%D1%80%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B5%D1%88%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%86%D0%B0,_%D0%A7%D0%B8%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8_%D0%B4%D0%BE_%D0%A1%D0%B0%D0%BC%D1%83%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B0_%D0%9A%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BF%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82.jpg)

Strumeshnitsa river, in Natura 2000 protected zone [Rupite-
Strumeshnitsa](https://bg.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%A0%D1%83%D0%BF%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B5_-_%D0%A1%D1%82%D1%80%D1%83%D0%BC%D0%B5%D1%88%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%86%D0%B0).
Photo by Georgy Palpurin, ShareBulgaria team via Wikimedia Commons CC BY-SA
4.0.

This year, [nine of the Central and Eastern European
countries](http://wikilovesearth.org/en/how-wiki-loves-earth-goes-in-cee-
countries/) are organizing the national stages of the “Wiki Loves Earth” photo
competition. This photo contest complements the regional [article writing
contest “CEE
Spring,”](https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Wikimedia_CEE_Spring_2017) which
aims to support content creation about the region and includes a category
dedicated to nature and geography.

In Bulgaria the “Wiki Loves Earth” competition was organized for the third
time in a row, from June 1 to 30.

[![](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/08/Participating_Countries_WLE_2017.svg_.png)](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Participating_Countries_WLE_2017.svg/512px-
Participating_Countries_WLE_2017.svg.png)

Participating Countries Wiki Loves Earth 2017. Image by Saqib, CC BY-SA 4.0.

“The basic aim of the competition is to collect photos of natural heritage
sites – such as nature reserves, landscape conservation areas, national parks,
scenic/landscape areas, remarkable gardens, etc. – to illustrate articles in
the worldwide free encyclopedia Wikipedia and other Wikimedia Foundation
projects,” states the official announcement of the global competition.

The 2017 edition of the “Wiki Loves Earth” contest includes participants from
a total of 37 countries on five different continents. Organizers and
contributors have been using the hashtag
[#WikiLovesEarth](https://twitter.com/hashtag/WikiLovesEarth?src=hash) to
publish photos and promote a spirit of sharing.

Over 137,000 photos have been collected on a global level so far, with India,
Germany, Ukraine, Brazil and Pakistan as top contributors.

